        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 5:41PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 541 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles northeast of Greenville Downtown, or near Greer, moving south
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Greer, Duncan, Lyman, GSP Airport, and Wellford.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
